    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Innsbruck, 16 May 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He has understood from Oláh’s letter that the
                            counties have to be written to individually in his (i.e. the King’s)
                            name, he will sign these to approve them and send them back to be
                            furnished with the Hungarian seal. 2. As for the shared mandates, in
                            which he orders the estates to obey Maximilian in his absence, indeed
                            they will have to proceed with more care lest they provoke fear, so it
                            can wait for a month, until he returns. In the meantime, Maximilian
                            should go ahead and sign in everyday cases, and Oláh should sign as
                            Chancellor. 3. As to the rumours about some kinds of practices, Oláh
                            should try to look into it, and if he finds something out, he should
                            tell Maximilian. In addition, he should know that he has told Maximilian
                            to meet the Polish King’s envoy and Mathias Loboczki on his (King
                            Ferdinand I’s) behalf.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Reverendissime in Christo Pater, Fidelis Sincere nobis Dilecte!</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Intelleximus ex litteris tuis decima huius mensis die ad nos
                        datis,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">We do not know this letter.</note>
                    quibus causis et rationibus permoti fueritis <del corresp="scriba">tot dampnum
                        consultaretur de dandis in singulos comitatus litteris</del> eam sequi et
                    amplecti opinionem, ut litterae, <del corresp="scriba">quae</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">quas</add> in negotio subsidii in proximo
                    conventu oblati in singulos comitatus scribi oportere visum est, nomine nostro
                    conficerentur, et cum huius consilii in opinionis ratio nobis quoque <del
                        corresp="scriba">probatae</del><add corresp="scriba" type="corr"
                        >clementer</add> probaretur, litteras ipsas ad nos transmissas manu nostra
                    subscripsimus ibique illas sigillo nostro Hungarico sigillandas et ad comitatus
                    transmittendas cum praesentibus remittimus. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Quantum <del corresp="scriba">ad</del> autem ad mandata illa
                    publica attinet, quibus regni statibus atque ordinibus praeciperetur, ut nobis
                    absentibus serenissimum principem dominum <persName>Maximilianum</persName>
                    regem Bohemiae etc. filium nostrum carissimum, tamquam nos ipsos <milestone
                        unit="pb"/>audire et illi obtemperare deberent, visum est nobis, re
                    diligenter perpensa et considerata, si huiusmodi mandata a nobis emitterentur,
                        <del corresp="scriba">omnes in hanc opinionem et cogitatinem facile
                        venturam</del> quod facile ea apud omnes suspicio oriretur, <del
                        corresp="scriba">quasi</del> nos a regno nostro Hungariae et provinciis
                    istis Austriacis <del corresp="scriba">alio valde</del> longo tempore abesse
                    statuisset, et sic multi <del corresp="scriba">ex fidelibus nostris</del>
                    fidelium nostrorum ex huiusmodi opinata diuturna absentia nostra in timorem
                    coniecerentur. Adversariis vero et eis, qui fortasse occulta consilia et
                    practicas aliquas cogitant, eo maior ausa praeberetur <del corresp="scriba"
                        >sinistris huiusmodi</del> non solum <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">eo
                        magis sinistra quaeque</add> cogitandi, sed etiam suscipiendi <del
                        corresp="scriba">cum sperarent se</del>, sicuti <del corresp="scriba"
                        >cum</del> in ipse <del corresp="scriba">facile</del> pro tua prudentia
                    facile perpendere et cogitare potes. Cum igitur omnino speremus <del
                        corresp="scriba">brevi</del> nos <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">dante
                        Deo brevi in spatio videlicet unius mensis</add> istuc redituros, consultius
                    esse existimavimus dictorum <milestone unit="pb"/>mandatorum publicationem et
                    emissionem hoc quidem tempore differendam. Interim autem volumus, ut litterae in
                    negotiis communibus et quotidianis <add corresp="scriba" type="insert"
                        >nihilominus sub</add> praefati serenissimi filii nostri regis
                        <persName>Maximiliani</persName> nomine et titulo conficiantur, ac per te
                        <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">tamquam cancellarium</add> pro more
                    solito primum et deinde per dilectionem eius subscribantur, et denique solito
                    dilectionis sub sigillo obsignentur. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[3.] <del corresp="scriba">Ea quae de rumoribus</del> Quod ad <del
                        corresp="scriba">veros</del> rumores <del corresp="scriba">attinet</del>,
                    qui ad te de practicis quibusdam afferantur, attinet, te clementer hortamur et
                    requirimus, ut <del corresp="scriba">tamquam atque in</del> diligentem operam
                    adhibeas, ut quantum per te fieri potest, rerum explorationem <del
                        corresp="scriba">hanc</del> habeas, et quicquid ad te perlatum fuerit, nobis
                    et serenissimo filio nostro significare non praetermittas. <del corresp="scriba"
                        >Quod</del> Postremo nolumus <del corresp="scriba">devotionem tuam</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">te</add> latere nos <del corresp="scriba">in
                            <gap extent="unknown" reason="illegible" unit="word"/></del> praefato
                    serenissimo filio nostro regi <persName>Maximiliano</persName> commisisse, ut et
                        <persName>oratorem</persName> serenissimi <persName>regis
                        Poloniae</persName> et magnificum <persName>Mathiam Loboczky</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Mathias Loboczki was a Counsellor of King
                        Ferdinand I, and Lord of Tarkő, see <hi rend="smallcap">Wagner</hi> 1774,
                        passim.</note><milestone unit="pb"/><del corresp="scriba">a</del> in ipsorum
                    relatibus audire et <del corresp="scriba">nobis ea quae exposuerint</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">nostro nomine</add> velit. Haec itaque sunt,
                    quae tibi ad praedictas litteras tuas clementer respondenda duximus.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Datum <placeName>Oeniponti</placeName> die 16. Maii 1552.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso" xml:id="d.2">
                <head>Probably on the other side:</head>
                <p xml:id="p.6"> Agriensi.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
